  "description": "This algorithm identifies the Bollinger Bands' contraction to the lowest 10th percentile, signaling a potential breakout. It executes trades based on the subsequent expansion phase, aiming to capitalize on volatility shifts in the 30-minute timeframe.",
  "algorithm_type": "TechnicalPattern",
  "prompt": "Design an expert-level TechnicalPattern trading algorithm in Python format that exploits the expansion and contraction phases of the Bollinger Bands (\u201cBollinger Squeeze\u201d) on the 30-minute timeframe. Entry signal: Identify when the Bollinger Bands\u2019 width (standard deviation bands using a 20-period Simple Moving Average and 2 standard deviations) contracts to the lowest 10th percentile of its past 120 periods, then wait for a breakout: initiate a long position if price closes above the upper band or a short if price closes below the lower band within the next 5 bars after contraction. Exit: close the position when price returns inside the bands or when stop-loss/take-profit of 1 ATR (Average True Range, 14-period) is hit. Include logic to avoid new trades if an open position already exists.",
